OL,3,COne second glory for Belfast City
OL,4,CMarathon winner
OL,6,FThousands of people have been taking
OL,7,Fpart in the 44th Belfast City Marathon.
OL,9,FAround 23,000 runners and joggers
OL,10,Fstarted the race at Stormont Estate at
OL,11,F9am before finishing in Ormeau Park on
OL,12,FSunday.
OL,14,FSpectators lined much of the 26.2 mile
OL,15,Froute to support those taking part.
OL,17,FAbay Alemu won the 2026 marathon in a
OL,18,Ftime of 2:16:23, just one second ahead
OL,19,Fof second place winner Teadese Mamo.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/3
